   158â†’    """
   159â†’    Instrument the target function to perform run-time type checking.
   160â†’
   161â†’    This decorator recompiles the target function, injecting code to type check
   162â†’    arguments, return values, yield values (excluding ``yield from``) and assignments to
   163â†’    annotated local variables.
   164â†’
   165â†’    This can also be used as a class decorator. This will instrument all type annotated
   166â†’    methods, including :func:`@classmethod <classmethod>`,
   167â†’    :func:`@staticmethod <staticmethod>`,  and :class:`@property <property>` decorated
   168â†’    methods in the class.
   169â†’
   170â†’    .. note:: When Python is run in optimized mode (``-O`` or ``-OO``, this decorator
   171â†’        is a no-op). This is a feature meant for selectively introducing type checking
   172â†’        into a code base where the checks aren't meant to be run in production.
   173â†’
   174â†’    :param target: the function or class to enable type checking for
   175â†’    :param forward_ref_policy: override for
   176â†’        :attr:`.TypeCheckConfiguration.forward_ref_policy`
   177â†’    :param typecheck_fail_callback: override for
