    61â†’) -> Any:
    62â†’    """
    63â†’    Ensure that ``value`` matches ``expected_type``.
    64â†’
    65â†’    The types from the :mod:`typing` module do not support :func:`isinstance` or
    66â†’    :func:`issubclass` so a number of type specific checks are required. This function
    67â†’    knows which checker to call for which type.
    68â†’
    69â†’    This function wraps :func:`~.check_type_internal` in the following ways:
    70â†’
    71â†’    * Respects type checking suppression (:func:`~.suppress_type_checks`)
    72â†’    * Forms a :class:`~.TypeCheckMemo` from the current stack frame
    73â†’    * Calls the configured type check fail callback if the check fails
    74â†’
    75â†’    Note that this function is independent of the globally shared configuration in
    76â†’    :data:`typeguard.config`. This means that usage within libraries is safe from being
    77â†’    affected configuration changes made by other libraries or by the integrating
    78â†’    application. Instead, configuration options have the same default values as their
    79â†’    corresponding fields in :class:`TypeCheckConfiguration`.
    80â†’
    81â†’    :param value: value to be checked against ``expected_type``
    82â†’    :param expected_type: a class or generic type instance, or a tuple of such things
    83â†’    :param forward_ref_policy: see :attr:`TypeCheckConfiguration.forward_ref_policy`
    84â†’    :param typecheck_fail_callback:
    85â†’        see :attr`TypeCheckConfiguration.typecheck_fail_callback`
    86â†’    :param collection_check_strategy:
    87â†’        see :attr:`TypeCheckConfiguration.collection_check_strategy`
    88â†’    :return: ``value``, unmodified
    89â†’    :raises TypeCheckError: if there is a type mismatch
    90â†’
    91â†’    """
